President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of North Carolina due to the impact of Tropical Storm Eta from November 12 to November 15, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available for emergency work, as well as the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in certain counties. Hazard mitigation measures will also receive federal funding on a cost-sharing basis statewide. Myra M. Shird has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.